quran[13]{c,v,t,f}:
35,45,"If Allah were to take people to task for their deeds, He would not leave any living creature on earth, but He grants them respite to an appointed time. When their appointed time comes to an end, surely Allah fully observes His servants."
36,1,"Ya'. Sin. {1}",footnotes:1:Ibn Abbas
36,2,"By the Wise Qur'an,"
36,3,"you are truly among the Messengers, {1}",footnotes:1:To begin a discourse like this does not mean that the Prophet (peace be upon him)
36,4,"on a Straight Way,"
36,5,"(and this Qur'an) is a revelation from the Most Mighty, the Most Compassionate {1}",footnotes:1:Here
36,6,"so that you may warn a people whose ancestors were not warned before wherefore they are heedless. {1}",footnotes:1:Another translation can be: You should warn the people of the same of which their forefathers had been warned
36,7,"Surely most of them merit the decree of chastisement; so they do not believe. {1}",footnotes:1:This is about those people who were being obstinate and stubborn with regard to the message of the Prophet (peace be upon him) and had made up their minds not to listen to him at all. This is because: They have already deserved the torment; therefore
36,8,"We have put fetters around their necks which reach up to their chins so that they are standing with their heads upright, {1}",footnotes:1:“Shackles” in this verse implies their own stubbornness which was preventing them from accepting the truth. “Reaching to chins” and “so they are made stiff-necked” implies the stiffness of the neck which is caused by pride and haughtiness. Allah means to impress this: We have made their obstinacy and stubbornness the shackles of their neck
36,9,"and We have put a barrier before them and a barrier behind them, and have covered them up, so they are unable to see. {1}",footnotes:1:Setting a barrier before them and a barrier behind them
36,10,"It is all the same for them whether you warn them or do not warn them for they shall not believe. {1}",footnotes:1:This does not mean that it is futile to preach
36,11,"You can warn only him who follows the Admonition and fears the Merciful Lord without seeing Him. Give such a one good tidings of forgiveness and a generous reward."
36,12,"We shall surely raise the dead to life and We record what they did and the traces of their deeds that they have left behind. {1} We have encompassed that in a Clear Book.",footnotes:1:This shows that three kinds of the entries are made in the conduct-book of men. First
